'''Ōtomo no Fukei''' (大伴 吹負) was a military leader during the {{ill|Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代}} in Japan. His name is also recorded as '''Otoko Fukei''' or '''Ko Fukei''' (小吹負). His {{ill|kabane|ja|カバネ}} was {{ill|Muraji|ja|連}}. He was a son of {{ill|Ōtomo no Kujii|ja|大伴咋}}, who held the rank of {{ill|Ōdoku|ja|大徳}}. Fukei's posthumous rank was {{ill|Jū Daikin Middle|ja|大錦中}}, and he also served as the governor of {{ill|Hitachi Province|ja|常陸国}}. [[Category:Ōtomo no Fukei]] [[Category:Completion tier 4]][[Category: tier 4]] [[Category:11]] [[sn:Ōtomo no Fukei]] [[Category:11]] [[Category:11]] [[sn:Ōtomo no Fukei]] [[Category:11]] [[Category:11]] [[sn:Ōtomo no Fukei]] [[Category:11]] [[Category:Ōtomo no Fukei]] [[Category:Ōtomo no Fukei]]
